    <abstract-text>This paper analyzes the genetic basis and modern conception of molecular
        mechanisms of recognition of pathogens, mainly viruses, by plants. The importance of signal
        systems and their key factors in plant organisms are discussed. The possible role of
        different elicitors in signal transduction processes is reviewed.</abstract-text>
